---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What kind of towel do you use in a sauna?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most sauna-goers use either a Turkish peshtemal towel or a standard cotton terry towel. Turkish towels are preferred because they are lightweight, dry fast, and do not absorb as much moisture as terry cloth — meaning they stay manageable during a long session. A second towel sits on the bench to protect the wood and absorb sweat."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What size towel do you need for a sauna?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For bench coverage: a standard bath towel (27x52 inches) covers most bench widths. For wrapping: a large bath towel or towel wrap (35x60 inches minimum) works comfortably. Turkish towels in the 37x70 inch range are the most versatile — large enough to sit on, wrap around, and use as a drying towel."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Base
  title="Best Sauna Towels (2025): What Actually Works"
  description="The best towels for sauna use. What material works, what size you need, and which picks are worth buying for bench use and wrapping."
  canonical="/guides/best-sauna-towels"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">Best Sauna Towels (2025)</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-500 mb-8">Updated January 2025 &mdash; Backyard Sauna Pro</p>

    <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
      <img src="/images/lifestyle/sauna-benches-stones.jpg" alt="Sauna bench with towel" class="w-full object-cover max-h-80" loading="lazy" width="1200" height="800" />
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8 text-sm text-stone-700">
      <strong>Affiliate disclosure:</strong> As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This page contains affiliate links.
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 mb-6">Sauna towels do two jobs: protect the bench from sweat and give you something to wrap up in between rounds. The wrong towel is too heavy, takes forever to dry, and mildews. Here is what works.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Turkish Towels vs Terry Cloth</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">Turkish peshtemal towels are the clear winner for sauna use. They are woven cotton (no loops), which means they dry much faster than terry cloth, take up less space, and hold less water weight during a session. A standard terry towel soaked with sweat feels heavy and stays wet. A Turkish towel wrings out almost dry and is comfortable in minutes.</p>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">The tradeoff: Turkish towels feel less plush than terry. If you want a thick wrap after the sauna, have a terry robe or towel waiting outside. Use the Turkish towel inside.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-6">Top Picks</h2>

    <div class="space-y-5 mb-10">
      <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <div>
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 bg-amber-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wide">Best Overall</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-1">Turkish Peshtemal Towel (37x70")</h3>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4 text-sm">100% cotton, fast-drying, large enough to sit on and wrap around. Buy 2-3 so you always have a dry one. The most practical sauna towel for the money.</p>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=turkish+peshtemal+towel+sauna+cotton&tag=backyardsauna-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-block bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">Browse Turkish Towels on Amazon</a>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
          <div>
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-stone-600 bg-stone-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wide">Best Bench Cover</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-1">Sauna Bench Towel / Seat Pad</h3>
          </div>
          
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4 text-sm">Dedicated bench towels or pads are cut wide to cover the full bench surface and often have a non-slip backing. Worth having if you use the sauna daily — they protect the cedar better than draping a regular towel.</p>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=sauna+bench+towel+cover+cotton&tag=backyardsauna-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-block border border-amber-400 text-amber-700 font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-amber-50 transition-colors">Browse Bench Towels on Amazon</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">How Many Towels Do You Need?</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 mb-8 ml-4 text-sm">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Bench cover:</span> 1 per person per session (sits under you on the bench)</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Body wrap:</span> 1 per person (wear between rounds or to walk to the cold plunge)</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Drying towel:</span> 1 per person after the final rinse</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Total minimum:</span> 2 towels per person. Buy 6 total for a couple so there is always a clean set ready</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Care and Maintenance</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">Sauna towels need washing after every session — they absorb sweat and sitting moisture. Avoid fabric softener (it coats cotton fibers and reduces absorption). Dry thoroughly before folding and storing; damp folded towels mildew fast. Turkish towels hold up fine in regular laundry but soften and become more absorbent with each wash.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">What kind of towel do you use in a sauna?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">Turkish peshtemal cotton towels are the best choice — fast-drying, lightweight, and comfortable. One sits under you on the bench, one wraps around you between rounds.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">What size towel for a sauna?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">37x70 inches is the most versatile. Large enough to sit on fully, wrap around the body, and use as a drying towel after.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6 mt-10">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Related</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><a href="/guides/best-sauna-accessories" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Best Sauna Accessories</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/sauna-gift-ideas" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Sauna Gift Ideas</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/what-to-wear-in-sauna" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">What to Wear in a Sauna</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/sauna-etiquette" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Sauna Etiquette Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
